                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>STATE OF NEW YORK&#44;<lb/>
                Assembly Chamber<lb/></p>
            <p>Albany&#44; Mch 27 1888<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev Dr S Morais<lb/>
                My dear Sir<lb/></p>
            <p>I have written to Dr<lb/> Cohen asking him as to what Sunday he could come<lb/> over&#44; and arrange to have you here&#44; so that you&#44;<lb/> Dr Cohen&#44; Piza&#44; Cowen &#38; myself&#44; might have<lb/> a thorough look at and into&#44; the Students&#44; and<lb/> see how far we are justified in giving them stipends&#44;<lb/> in view of their future probabilities &#38;c&#45;&#45;<lb/> It will be necessary that a couple of hours<lb/> say from 2 to 4&#44; some Sunday&#44; shall be given<lb/> to this necessary work&#45;&#45;Another matter&#45;&#45;<lb/>we must get our Seminary Report printed and<lb/> out for general circulation&#45;&#45;your address&#44; really<lb/> admirable&#44; will hardly do as it is for a Report&#45;&#45;<lb/> could you not add to it some statements as to<lb/> Students&#44; Studies &#38;c &#38;c&#44; which you can get<lb/> from Dr Drachmans report to you&#45;&#45;or if you<lb/> prefer Dr D can make such a report&#45;&#45;it<lb/> might however never be included in yours&#45;&#45;<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>I hope you are enjoying the Passover&#45;&#45;<lb/> Yours truly<lb/> Joseph Blumenthal<lb/></p>
            </body>
    </text>
